etter hospitals) doctors to take their places. <br /><br />UT Hospital, where my mom worked for 15 yrs is a good example.  They went from being one of the top medical centers in the southeast to having to shut down 1/3 of their facilities and finding themselves unable to get any good doctors to work there.  Why?  Because of what was jsut described above: UT HAS to take ppl on Tenncare, and they get paid a FRACTION of what they would normally get paid for the same visits/procedures/etc.  The best and brightest in the medical field aren't going to put up with making a fraction of what they could be making for very long.  Most of em quit and go to private hospitals.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />I'm not at all surprised a health clinic wouldn't take you without some form of id.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I was shocked.  I had my birth certificate, SS Card,a wallet full of cash, and an OBVIOUSLY swollen face.  And gawddammit it HURT!<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Also, it costs a fortune to run an ER.  I don't know who upthread said most ER's are run by teaching hospitals- but that isn't the case.  In fact, in the hundred or so hospitals I've been in over the last four years or so, I haven't run into one where this was the situation.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Xuaxua wouldn't have made that kind of statement without knowing what he was talking about.  Surely you're somehow mistaken.<br /><br />(hey, I get to take a cheap shot every once in a while, too) <img src="images/jester_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br /><br />edit: I shouldn't say that "UT can't get any good doctors," there's a lot of good doctors there, but a LOT of the specialists have long-since left for greener pastures, and they ain't coming back.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
