                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> *steps out on a limb*<br /><br />I am willing to bet, unless your beliefs drive you to the point of "eccentric" that if you had children ( i HOPE you don't) that your views on ALOT of subject would change over time.<br /><br />My parents were divorced when i was 1.5 years old (born in sweden) I lived with my father until I was 12ish, moved in with my mom and stepdad.. pretty poor, lived on a 5 acre ranch (owned by developers with plans to develop when the time came so it was VERY cheap but we had no help when the septic went bad or electrical went bad.. house was over 85 years old) I went to school in name only but graduated from continuation school.. during my youth I trained horses rode saddle bronc a bit but from the day I was 15 had a job stocking beers and sodas at the truckstop down the road.. my parents made all their money "under the table". I never thought about it much until recently. I joined the millitary and lasted a year or so (leave+ drugs = bad) worst mistake I ever made.. but anyway.. I never planned to get married or have children.. <br /><br />long story short.. I met a girl (my boss at the time) got married and had kids /boggle one thing led to another, got a loan, went to tech school,  and boom I end up a developer for an ISP and pay half my pay in taxes. I HATE paying taxes but I would NEVER work to avoid Uncle Sam.. why? because my children would suffer. I would loose my house, cars, wife, and ultimately my children.<br /><br />I tend to think that the values you seem to find so important, contradict the necissary requirements placed (forced?) upon you by the government. You steal the services, you take un-due advantage of every day. Any time you use public infrastructure or any public amenity your stealing from the people who pay taxes to provide those services. Your not living by standards others do, yet you make the choice to use our services. sounds a bit dishonest, no matter how you slice it. Given the gift of children would you attitude change?<br /><br />*Edit: edumication hard at wurk <img src="images/apple_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
