                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><i>Originally posted by Usildor</i><br /><br />A few points..<br /><br />You make several stances about a person being a "resident of their state" and not "the corporate United States"...so in this we assume that based on previous arguments you made that you DO PAY STATE INCOME TAXES, correct?<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />There is no state income tax here in TN.  They tried to pass one a coupole of yrs ago, the blowback was a beautiful thing to behold.  I bet few politicos will dare mention it again any time soon.<br /><br />But to answer what Im sure your next question would be, WOULD I pay state income tax? Fuck no.  My point was that from a legalese standpoint, most folks are citizens of their respective sates and not the corporate United States of America (inc), and are not liable to be taxed by said corporation, blah blah.  Again, I'm no expert in the legalese of it all but that's sorta how it goes.  I have offered (and it is a standing offer) to give a list of attorneys that can and will (usually for free, or for what you can afford to pay) explain this to anyone thaty wants to PM me the state they live in.<br /><br />I personally dont go for the legalese, but a discussion of such erupted anyway. I'd hide my income from the thieves in TN too, should they come looking for it.  You should, too.  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Also, one court case you quoted from 1906 states " a person shall not be required to do any thing" which is pretty vague...but my main point is (and I'm not sure of this) but wasnt this WELL BEFORE income taxes were instituted?<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Yeah, so?  Does a Supreme Court ruling ever become invalid because a later "law" (which was never lawfully passed) violates the ruling?<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Also, since you say you dont suck from the teat....you are no longer eligible for<br />Assistance or protection from police<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />That's fine.  When I compare the times in my life that I've "needed" a cop to the times in my life that I've been unecessarily (i.e. without good reason or probable cause) harassed, detained, ASSAULTED (more than once) and just plain treated like a peice of shit by our "public servants," I think doing without would be a worthy trade off.  Most people, if having to make an honest comparison, would probably be forced to come to the same conclusion, although perhaps not as vehemently.<br /><br />Privatize the police and arm the public.  Let the folks that provide the best SERVICE for the best cost get paid to do the job.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Protection by military<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Privatize that too.  Our gvmnt military is too busy "protecting" the rest of the world right now, anyway.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Assistance in emergency of fire<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Neighborhood volunteer fire department.  Rural living &gt; city life for more reasons than one.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Education for any future children in any tax funded body (public schools, state universities, etc)<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I would never DREAM of sending my kids to public school for indoctrination, are you kidding?  Same for most universities.  I went to a "private" college (ITT and some time at TN Institute of Electronics), and I paid for it.  Interestingly, those schools aren't a cesspool of liberalism (i.e. socialism) like state universities are.  Wonder why?<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />any subsidized housing<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I already believe that I don't have a "right" to subsidized housing.  Neither does anybody else.  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Just want to make sure you dont or ever plan on having those things.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I dont.<br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />You are IMO not deserving of protection under the constitution since it is the job of the judiciary branch to enforce it and that arm of the gov is funded directly by taxes.  <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I don't need "protection under the constitution" and neither do you.  We're human beings with GOD-GIVEN rights to life and liberty.  Constitutions are among those things that seek to curtail such god-given rights.  There's the fundamental flaw in your thinking, in my humble opinion.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Have a nice day :)<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />You too :D<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
